  <article>
    <title>Problems</title>
    <section>
      <list>
	<item>Government bodies such as Arkivverket publish archive standards.</item>
	<item>Vendors write scripts that sometimes are incompliant with standards.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
  </article>
  <article>
    <title>Standard</title>
    <section>
      <p>The switch from DTD to XSD in Noark 4 to Noark 5 made the standard stronger, but still requires correct JSON parsing of endpoints and implementation of the formal standard.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
  <article>
    <title>Audience</title>
    <section>
      <p>Document Controllers and Record Keepers can point at Noark 5 for best practise.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
  <article>
    <title>Separation of Data and Structure with MVC</title>
    <section>
      <p>Model View Controller is a concept conceived by Trygve Reenskaug at Xerox PARC in a note on MVC in 1978.</p>
      <p>The MVC note defines 4 terms: Model, View, Controller and Editor.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
